IDENTIFY the tendons crossing the anterior aspect of the

Identify the muscle belly located most medially. This is the tibialis anterior muscle. Follow the tendon of the tibialis anterior across the anterior aspect of the talocrural joint to its point of attachment on the medial aspect of the foot. What action, in addition to dorsiflexion of the talocrural joint, does the tibialis anterior contribute to? Think of your answer before clicking here:     . What muscle, located in the posterior deep compartment, also attaches to the medial aspect of the foot and has the same action as TA? Think first! 
Now identify the muscle belly located most laterally. It is the extensor digitorum longus. Follow its tendon into the foot and note that it forms four tendons, which cross the superior aspect of the lateral four toes. What is the action of this muscle? Think first, click second!
Identify, intermediate between the tibialis anterior and extensor digitorum longus, the muscle belly of the extensor hallucis longus. Follow its tendon into the foot and across the superior aspect of the great toe. What is the action of the extensor hallucis longus? Think then click!

Extensor digitorum longus extends lateral four toes. 
FYI: You may notice a tendinous offshoot of extensor digitorum longus inserting in the area of the base of the fifth metatarsal. It is part of extensor digitorum longus that some call the fibularis tertius.
Extensor hallucis longus extends great toe.
